Package: tritonIngest
Title: Tabular Data Ingestion Toolkit
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R:
    person("Travis", "Shepherd", email = "travis.shepherd@tritonenv.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Domain-agnostic primitives for ingesting messy field and laboratory
    data workbooks: all-as-text reading of CSV/TSV/XLSX, long/wide layout
    detection and reshaping, declarative column contracts with synonym and fuzzy
    auto-mapping, reusable JSON column-mapping profiles, non-detect (left-
    censored) value parsing and substitution, and unit reconciliation. Shared by
    the water-chemistry-qaqc and bw-analysis-code projects so each can reuse the
    same ingestion plumbing without duplicating it. Contains no domain knowledge,
    statistics, or plotting.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    jsonlite,
    purrr,
    readr,
    readxl,
    stats,
    tibble,
    tidyr,
    tools,
    utils
Suggests:
    arrow,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
